==Old Norse==
===Etymology===
{{af|non|Yggr|drasill||t1=the terrifying one; Odin|t2=steed}}, where “steed” refers to a hanging tree or possibly from {{m|ine-pro|*dʰer-||to hold, support}}, in any case referring to the story of Odin hanging himself on the tree for nine nights.
